cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper discusses the integration of graph processing into an in-memory relational database, which is relevant to several sub-categories. cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the integration of graph processing into a relational database management system. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also relevant as the paper discusses the challenges of processing graphs natively inside a relational engine. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of graph processing in various domains, such as biological networks. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper proposes a new approach for processing graphs natively inside a relational engine. cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of SQL and query engines to declaratively define graphs and execute cross-data-model query plans.
